    <text>
        <body>
            <div style="handwritten" type="letter" xml:id="d.1">
                <head type="title">Camillo Ghilino to Miklós Oláh (Milan, 9 November 1534)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p xml:id="reg.p.1">He will keep it brief because the bearer of the letter
                            is hurrying him. The Pope’s death has helped the Emperor’s affairs a
                            lot, the new Pope will not be against him. Lodovico Gritti has deserved
                            his punishment, if only King Francis I met the same fate. Lucretia
                            Caballis will report on the Bey of Tunis and Hayreddin Barbarossa Pasha.
                        </p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb facs="https://www.eleveltar.hu/kereso-portlet/spring/digitalcontent/getcontent/preservica/27A2D118-D7AB-4085-9171-0E52C9B9DD38
                    "/>
                <p xml:id="p.1">Idem Nicolao Olao salutem. </p>
                <p xml:id="p.2">Breviorem me facit tabellarii festinatio, quam institueram, quare,
                    mihi ignoscas, velim. <persName>Clementis</persName><note xml:id="note.1">Pope
                        Clement VII died on 25 September, 1534.</note> interitus, di boni, quantum
                    rebus <persName>caesaris</persName> Dei nostri conduxit, mira certe cum
                        <persName>Gallo</persName><note xml:id="note.2">King Francis I.</note>
                    sempiterno hoste nostro in conventu illo Massaliensi fabricaverat, quae brevi
                    exibunt. Novus <persName>pontifex</persName><note xml:id="note.3">Pope Paul III,
                        born Alessandro Farnese.</note> caesari haud adversabitur, nobisque aequus
                    erit omnium consensu et opinione. <persName>Griteus</persName><note
                        xml:id="note.4">Lodovico Gritti.</note> sceleratus poenas meritas a Dacis
                    suis luit, utinam et Gallus omnium regum, qui sunt et qui fuerunt, pessimus, cum
                    Turca suo illud idem committat. Quod de <persName>regulo Tuneti</persName>,<note
                        xml:id="note.5">Abu Abdallah Muhammad V al-Hasa.</note> item
                        <persName>Aenobarbi</persName> classe habemus, de <choice>
                        <orig>Lucretiae Virgine</orig>
                        <supplied><persName>Lucretia Virgine</persName></supplied>
                    </choice><note xml:id="note.6">Lucretia Caballis (vom Ross).</note> rarissima
                    intelliges. Istae enim exempla quaedam litterarum <persName>duci</persName><note
                        xml:id="note.7">Francesco II Sforza.</note> meo transmissa exaravi. Vale et
                        <persName>Bannisium</persName><note xml:id="note.8">Jakob Radich de Bannisis
                        the Younger.</note> nostrum salutabis et, quid actum fuerit de globo meo
                    aliquando, scribe. </p>
                <p xml:id="p.3"><placeName>Mediolano</placeName> IX. Novembris 1534.</p>
            </div>
